    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-09-23T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-09-23T04:00:00-05:00" n="706"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d706">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500a4/191: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Warren</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-09-23T18:00:00+09:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 23, 1921—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 23—1:11 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>313. Following telegram received from consul, Dairen.</p>
                <pb facs="0843" n="747" xml:id="pg_747"/>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“September 23, 11 a.m. Referring to the American Government’s apparent
                        refusal to permit Far Eastern Republic to send delegates to Washington
                            Conference,<note n="52" xml:id="d706fn52">See telegram no. 545, Sept.
                            17, to the Ambassador in Great Britain, <ref target="frus1921v01#pg_69"
                                >vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 69</ref>.</note> Yurin
                        inquires if there is any objection to send trade mission from Chita.</p>
                </quote>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Warren</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
